---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="A note to you" description="A personal message from Julius.">
  <div class="text-page">
    <h1>A note to you</h1>

    <p>
      You're reading this because I wanted to share something with you — not just a recipe, but the way I cook.
      The things I make on a Tuesday when I don't know what else to do. The dishes that take twenty minutes
      and somehow feel like an occasion. The ones I've made so many times I've stopped measuring anything.
    </p>

    <p>
      Cooking is the best way I know to show someone you care. But I can't always be there to cook for you,
      so I built this instead.
    </p>

    <p>
      Every recipe here is something I've actually made — more than once, usually. The descriptions are honest.
      Some of them are easy, some are projects, a few are just a tin of tomatoes and some garlic and somehow it works.
    </p>

    <p>
      I hope you find something here that you want to make. And I hope when you do, it's good.
    </p>

    <p>
      — Julius
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
